Designing for high availability requires eliminating single points of failure.

Recommended practices include:

* Deploy across Availability Zones
* Use Load Balancers
* Implement geo-redundant storage
* Configure automatic failover
* Regularly test disaster recovery plans

For example, an online banking application distributes workloads across multiple zones to ensure uninterrupted service.

A real-life use case is healthcare systems where downtime can directly impact patient care.

These practices improve reliability and business continuity.
